ility with any newer versions. I want to solve this effectively and avoid running into further problems down the line.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"Vert.x Web Client 5.0.1 is self-contained for meaningful in-process HTTP/WebClient coverage, but it still pulls Netty 4.2.x and needs the same Java 25 native runtime unsafe-access properties already used for 5.0.0.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set native-test/runtime system properties for io.vertx:vertx-web-client:5.0.1: -Dsun.misc.unsafe.memory.access=allow and -Dio.netty.tryReflectionSetAccessible=true. The existing 5.0.0 scaffold already applies these only when libraryVersion == '5.0.0'; extend the guard for 5.0.1 or the relevant Vert.x 5.0.x range. No external service is required for core coverage; use an in-process Vert.x HttpServer with WebClient/WebClientSession/CachingWebClient/forms/redirects as applicable.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Optional vertx-auth-oauth2 support is declared optional by the artifact; do not add it unless tests intentionally exercise OAuth2-specific APIs.\",\n    \"Local Gradle and Native Image verification remain authoritative for whether these runtime properties are sufficient for the reported native-image run failure.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e3850cc476f76fe016a3f360ec6bc8196b2f60f2b6c1ad110\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 717, "output": 796, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24553, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782527488417, "responseId": "resp_0e3850cc476f76fe016a3f3600ddc88196a94217b2ae7b4618"}, "toolResults": []}
